*INV1:	well what we're going to do is .
%mor:	intj|well pron|what-Int-S1 aux|be-Fin-Ind-Pres-S1 verb|go-Part-Pres-S part|to verb|do-Inf-S aux|be-Fin-Ind-Pres-S3 .
%gra:	1|2|DISCOURSE 2|0|ROOT 3|4|AUX 4|2|ACL-RELCL 5|6|MARK 6|4|XCOMP 7|2|COP 8|2|PUNCT
@Comment:	A b c D e F G H I J K l m N o P Q r s t u y w x y z 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 8 9 101112
@Comment:	Chi wants to write her a b c's (maybe because they are written on the pad of paper) and EXPs and Mot try to convince her to write a letter. Chi declares that she wants to write a letter after she finishes writing the alphabet. Context notes say Chi rolling on floor when says she doesn't want to write. Chi copies the alphabet on her own while Mot talks to the EXPs. Then Chi wants to write Mot a letter but EXP discourages this and ends the activity. (Context notes say that Chi's brother and Mot's boyfriend have come in , but they aren't on the tape) Before Chi had written alphabet , though , MOT had initiated the <you tell me the words and I'll spell them> routine , so we do have her end of that. For a short transcript of Mot's short discussion with EXP about drugs and MSA's hand+writing see MSATALK5 on the MSA HV5 disk
